{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I certainly did not know, despite the fact that there was evidence that got back and that Roosevelt had made a-- President Roosevelt had made a statement about that Jews were being persecuted and some of them killed, it never struck me that it was at all of the degree which it later turned out to be, which we later found out to be.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I just didn't believe, or the newspapers didn't convey to me, that the persecution and extermination of Jews and gypsies was as great as it was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I just thought it was occasional throwing people into concentration camps, isolating them, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when I came-- got reassigned into OSS and then could go into their-- the secret reports, I really got the story and began to see what was what.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That would have been the end of May or the beginning of June of 1945.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OSS headquarters in Washington, DC.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, within a month I got myself shipped to Justice Jackson's staff and to that branch of it which was operating in Paris.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Documentation Division was actually operating in Paris.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first documents we had were the captured documents of the later defendant Alfred Rosenberg, who was the ideological sponsor of the Nazis from way back and who became the- the Reich Commissioner for the Ausland, for occupied Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the atrocities and the slave labor and the spoliation and all the things that he was involved in were just amazing, as shown by these documents.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I got to Paris in-- in June, Colonel Storey showed me these documents, which were lined up in two rooms.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were so-called Leitz ordners, very thick notebooks and very orderly-- kept in very orderly fashion.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
